msgctxt "an9.63:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.63:0.2"
msgid "7. Satipaṭṭhānavagga "
msgstr "7. Mindfulness Meditation "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 63. Sikkhādubbalyasutta → sikkhādubbalyasatipaṭṭhānasuttaṃ (bj) … satipaṭṭhānasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an9.63:0.3"
msgid "63. Sikkhādubbalyasutta "
msgstr "63. Weaknesses in Training and Mindfulness Meditation "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an9.63:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, sikkhādubbalyāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five weaknesses when you’re training. "

msgctxt "an9.63:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an9.63:1.3"
msgid "Pāṇātipāto, adinnādānaṃ, kāmesumicchācāro, musāvādo, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānaṃ—"
msgstr "Killing living creatures, stealing, sexual misconduct, lying, and using alcoholic drinks that cause negligence. "

msgctxt "an9.63:1.4"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca sikkhādubbalyāni. "
msgstr "These are the five weaknesses when you’re training. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an9.63:2.1"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ sikkhādubbalyānaṃ pahānāya cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvetabbā. "
msgstr "To give up these five weaknesses in your training you should develop the four kinds of mindfulness meditation. "

msgctxt "an9.63:2.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an9.63:2.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "an9.63:2.4"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "an9.63:2.5"
msgid "citte … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of the mind … "

msgctxt "an9.63:2.6"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "an9.63:2.7"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ sikkhādubbalyānaṃ pahānāya ime cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvetabbā”ti. "
msgstr "To give up those five weaknesses in your training you should develop these four kinds of mindfulness meditation.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.63:2.8"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

